events.name: Cloud Next Extended '18

group.name: GDG Springfield: Google Developer Group Springfield

events.description:
Please join GDG Springfield in our first Cloud Next Extended event! We are excited to bring the developer community in Springfield together to be a part of the Next '18 experience.

We plan on having some great local speakers, demos, and codelabs. Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $55 value, free of charge.

Bring a laptop if you want to participate in the codelab portion, and enjoy some delicious food and swag as well!

Additionally, we will be giving away a FREE Google Home Mini! Be there for a chance to win!

events.name: DevFest 2018

group.name: GDG Springfield: Google Developer Group Springfield

events.description:
#################################
IMPORTANT: RSVP http://sgfwebdevs.com/devfest
#################################

Schedule: https://devfestsgf.com/

Updated: Due to the multifaceted approach in planning with this event, there are now several event listings across social networks that you are able to RSVP at. For planning purposes we are asking that those of you who have already registered, please take a minute and fill out the new official form at http://sgfwebdevs.com/devfest

Thanks!

-------------------------------------

This will be an all day event and will conclude with a dev competition event in the evening.

We will have 3 prize drawings, throughout the day - make sure you're RSVP'd on the Google Form and present to be eligible!

Food and drinks will be provided.

-------------------------------------

Charlie Rosenbury & Enoch Bradshaw, Self Interactive
Beyond the flat screen: Getting Started in Augmented Reality Development

In this session, we will build a simple augmented reality experience and explore the similarities and differences from traditional 2D development.

This session will equip you with a foundational understanding of augmented reality development.

--------

Brenden Reeves, Marlin Network
Intro to Firebase Development with Android

Over the years Firebase has grown from a small database solution to a massive suite of development tools used by a variety of developers. I'll be going over the basics of what firebase is and walking through what it looks like to use Firebase as a backend for your Android app. We'll be looking at the built-in authentication services, cloud firestore, and the cloud messaging system.

--------

Jason Klein, Logic Forte
How to Retrain an Image Classifier for New Categories with TensorFlow

Retraining an existing Image Classification model is much easier than training a model from scratch. Jason will demonstrate how to retrain an existing Image Classifier to recognize images in two specific categories: Hotdog and NotHotdog.

--------

Jordan McAdoo,
iOS and Android Mobile development with Flutter

Come join this full-time native iOS developer as she explains what’s new and exciting about Flutter, with only a small amount of bias. Enjoy her experiences during a brief escape from Xcode while exploring this new SDK and what it has to offer.

--------

events.name: Holiday Party

group.name: GDG Springfield: Google Developer Group Springfield

events.description:
Please join Springfield Women in Tech and Springfield Google Developer Group for an end-of-year celebration!

This event is open to all. Feel free to bring guests with you.

There will be food and drink provided. More details are forthcoming, so mark your calendars now!

The party will have:

* a jukebox, no money required! Come and pick your favorite tunes!

* a photobooth, with unlimited prints! Get dressed up, and pick out your favorite props to make some memories you'll keep forever.

events.name: Internet of Things - Cloud Study Jam

group.name: GDG Springfield: Google Developer Group Springfield

events.description:
This event will include hands-on training and introduction into IoT using the Google Cloud Platform Console and Qwiklabs.

Food will be provided by Lindberg's and drinks will be provided as well!
We'll have giveaways, and free access to resources via Qwiklabs for attendees!

events.name: International Women's Day Celebration

group.name: GDG Springfield: Google Developer Group Springfield

events.description:
Join Springfield Women in Tech & Women Techmakers Springfield in a celebration of International Women's Day!

This event will kick off at 5pm with socialization, drinks, and food.
Food will be catered by Tea Bar & Bites Bakery and Café & include vegetarian-friendly options.

At 5:30pm we will begin a hands-on workshop (so bring your laptops, or pair up with friends!) going over building Actions for Google with guided instruction.

Around 7pm we will hear from a panel of local women speakers about their experiences in their fields. This panel includes:

* Dr. Tiffany Ford - department chair of Computer Science at Ozarks Technical Community College

* Ana Elliott - freelance writer, photographer, stylist; blogger/creator of http://www.shelearnsthings.com/

* Anne Mauldin - Director of Marketing and Public Relations at Mother's Brewing Company

* final panelist TBD

This event is open to all who want to celebrate women!
